main event: Several unidentified objects were observed near Farallon Islands, appearing to behave like missiles during the sighting.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 5 minutes with several objects tracked,Objects appeared to split into three trails without distortion of the South Plume,One object was described as moving much faster than a commercial jet and showed no visible exhaust, Radar contacts were made but evaluated as not a threat, The objects were suggested to possibly be balloons or aircraft.
witness description: A coast guard personnel and military observers involved in the reports
